subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Easily distinguished from similar congeners (other species of the 

arambourgi

species group and 

S. pallidus

) by second pair of apophyses frontally on male chelicerae (
Fig. 223
); also distinguished by tip of procursus (
Figs. 219, 220
), shapes of bulbal processes (pointed processes on dorsal projection; 
Figs. 221, 222
), and epigynum shape (frontal part with dark hexagonal area; 
Fig. 196
).
